This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to investigate and challenge the commonsense representation abilities of BERT, a popular deep contextual representation model. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML techniques for language processing. 

The paper also involves ML techniques such as fine-tuning and knowledge graph embeddings, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper involves image classification tasks, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to augment BERT's pretraining data, which is relevant to sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
